PCOA_Notes: Subset "AAB" and "AABA" shows that M.sp. Colymea clusters with M.urceolatus s.s. which is represented by the Pokolbin and Yengo populations. This group also includes Coolah Tops which bridges the group to its western extent in the Warrumbungles, Pilliga, Mt Kaputar and north of Narrabri. V. interestingly, this group is distinct from M.sp.new england and M.sp.Eukey. Though it divides M.sp. Inglewood as I had hypothesised that the north of narrabri pops would cluster with Bringalilly and early morphometrics showed an association.
